    "Each NDN router needs to check the signature and validity of the content, if the content signature is valid then the content will be forwarded, otherwise, it will be dropped as shown in Fig. 10.",
    "In the proposed scheme, when the router receives content or interest, it follows a few steps to validate the interest and content signature.",
    "The router subsequently caches the content once received.",
    "The router then checks the content with CCNCheck.",
    "Signatures are validated based on content probability."
